						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijayanagara, Narasimharāya = 1485-1495 A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Records a gift of a village by Pemmarasu-Uḍaiyar, the king's agent (kāriyattukku kaḍava), to the temples of Ardhanāriśvarara and Subrahmaṇya on the hill at Tiruchehengōḍu in Kīḻkarai-Pūnduṟai-nāḍu, a district of Koṅgu, <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Virachōḻa-maṇḍalam. The gift village was Chūrappaḷḷi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Akaram Maṇṇākki-nattam in the same <hi rend="italic">nāḍu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
